Hi guys! With Telegram bots trending recently its important to know how they work. The most important is that all the actions are executed from SERVER, not from your device. Every data is stored on SERVER as well. You create a wallet in TG bot? Its stored on server. You import your wallet? Its stored on server as well! Every time you communicate with bot, the message is first sent to Telegram server and then Telegram redirect this message to the server behind the bot. What does it mean? It means your keys are sent and stored somewhere that you dont have an access to. ...
